      itemCount={items.length}
      itemSize={50}
      width="100%"
      itemData={items}
    >
      {Row}
    </List>
  );
}
```

This will likely cut your render time dramatically — virtualization only renders the visible rows, so a list of 10,000 items behaves like a list of ~15. Pair it with `React.memo` on the Row component and you're good. Don't overthink it — this combo solves 90% of large list perf issues.

